  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Developing Citizenship in Martissant through FOKAL</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Demographically, Martissant is comprised of a majority of youth under 25. The daily violence in the neighborhood and the weak involvement of the state has important effects on the absence of security and well-being of the community, struck by unemployment, poverty and crime. In this context, youth are offered little opportunity to engage in public debate and civic integration. This project aims to address the question of civic education, in order to convey a better knowledge and understanding of civic, health and educational issues. It also offers youth the tools they need to build their own conscious, organic and reflective vision of the obstacles they face. The main objectives of the project are to train young people of Martissant on human rights and civics; to empower young people of Martissant with professional tools; and to empower local NGO&#x2019;s to enhance life skills for better psychological and physical health.</narrative>
  </description>
